						<div class="postbody"><em>(reads the a22 file)</em><br />Trying to make 6502 look like x86, I take it?<br /><br /><em>(tries the test on NTSC NES)</em><br />The text on the initial screen is somewhat cut off at the top. But here are some of my results:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">PPU RESET WAKE-UP TIME :0A7D&nbsp; &nbsp; 0A7D&nbsp; &nbsp; 0A7D<br />PPU WAKE-UP TO NMI TIME:002CBC&nbsp; 002CBB&nbsp; 2CBC<br />PPU NMI TO NMI TIME OFF:0B6651&nbsp; 0B6652&nbsp; 0B6651<br />PPU NMI TO NMI TIME ON :0B654E&nbsp; 0B654E&nbsp; 0B654E<br />PPU VBLANK DURATION&nbsp; &nbsp; :0038&nbsp; &nbsp; 0038&nbsp; &nbsp; 0038<br />PPU READ WITH DMC&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; :FAIL&nbsp; &nbsp; FAIL&nbsp; &nbsp; FAIL<br />JOY READ WITH DMC&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; :OK&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; OK&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; OK<br />PPU READ WITHOUT DMC&nbsp; &nbsp;:OK&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; OK&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; OK<br />JOY READ WITHOUT DMC&nbsp; &nbsp;:OK&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; OK&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; OK<br />PALETTE READ MONO-MODE :OK&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; OK&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; OK<br />PALETTE READ COLOR-MODE:FAIL&nbsp; &nbsp; FAIL&nbsp; &nbsp; OK<br /><br />00000010102020303030000010102020<br />00060E141C222A31383E060C141A2229<br /><br />00000010102020303030000010102020<br />00070E151C232A31383F060D141B2229<br /></div></div>

